From: LineageOS Desktop Project <noreply@local>
Subject: [PATCH] Launcher3: refresh IDP and recreate taskbar on display change

Patch summary:
Refresh Launcher3's cached device profile after primary display size or
density changes, and let the taskbar recreate itself across those changes so
the bar's window and contents track host resize events. The host window can
change size at runtime, and stale invariant profiles or stale taskbar window
attrs show up as wrongly sized app drawers and invisible taskbars.

Fix 2a: after the IDP refresh, push the new DeviceProfile into the all-apps
container. The IDP refresh notifies its registered listeners (the Launcher
activity, the DeviceProfile cache, the workspace), but
ActivityAllAppsContainerView caches its per-row count via setAppsPerRow()
inside onDeviceProfileChanged() and that callback is not on the IDP listener
chain. Without this explicit push, the workspace and taskbar recompute on
display resize but the all-apps grid renders with the per-row count from the
geometry that was in effect when the all-apps view was first laid out
(symptom: a narrow vertical strip of icons after dragging the scrcpy window
smaller).

Fix 2d: anchor the taskbar long-press popup against the taskbar bar's top
edge AND clamp against live window bounds. Two related bugs combined to send
the popup to the top of the screen:
  (a) PopupContainerWithArrow.getTaskbarTargetObjectLocation() used
      BaseDragLayer.getDescendantRectRelativeToSelf(originalView, ...), which
      returns the icon's layout rect. The taskbar parents its icons at the
      top of the drag layer and renders them at the bottom via a translation
      that the layout-rect walk does not reflect, so the anchor landed where
      the icon would be if the taskbar were not translated.
  (b) PopupContainerWithArrow.getCurrentDisplaySize() read dragLayer.height
      to compute maxY for clamping. The taskbar drag layer is wrap_content
      and reports height=0 during the popup's measure pass (before it
      expands around the popup), so preferredY got clamped down to minY=0
      regardless of where the anchor actually was.
Symptom: long-pressing a taskbar icon opened the popup at the top of the
screen rather than just above the bar, especially obvious when the popup is
tall enough that the bogus clamp can fire. Fix (a) by recomposing the target
rect from originalView.getLocationOnScreen() and the DeviceProfile-derived
taskbar height/bottomMargin; fix (b) by preferring WindowManager.current-
WindowMetrics over the wrap_content drag-layer size in getCurrentDisplaySize.
Result: popup hovers immediately above the bar with the existing
TASKBAR_POPUP_EXTRA_VERTICAL_OFFSET_PX gap, regardless of icon position.

Fix 2e: let CONFIG_ORIENTATION, CONFIG_SCREEN_SIZE, CONFIG_SCREEN_LAYOUT, and
CONFIG_SMALLEST_SCREEN_SIZE recreate the taskbar only on the desktop product
where the host window can resize dynamically. Upstream masks these bits to keep
the taskbar window alive across rotations on phones, so preserve that behavior
outside desktop/freeform displays. On desktop, the taskbar window's mAttrs
(notably the fillx<N> height) is baked in at window-create time. Without a
recreate, two rapid host-window resizes leave the window stuck at an
intermediate size, the bar's contents fail to lay out for the new geometry, and
the bar visually disappears even though the window remains visible to
WindowManager. Letting the normal recreate path fire for desktop displays means
the new taskbar comes up with mAttrs derived from the (R1-refreshed) DP and is
guaranteed to match the current screen.

Fix 2f: when TaskbarActivityContext.setTaskbarWindowSize is called with the
MATCH_PARENT sentinel (popup open, all-apps open, etc.), read the current
window bounds from WindowManager.getCurrentWindowMetrics() instead of the
cached mDeviceProfile.getDeviceProperties().getHeightPx(). The DP can lag a
host-window resize by one configuration change; using live currentWindow-
Metrics means the taskbar window's mAttrs height matches the current screen
the moment a fullscreen layout is requested. Same idiom as Fix 2d's
getCurrentDisplaySize change, applied at the window-attrs level so the
follow-up live-display-bounds patch can extract both into a reusable
ActivityContext.getLiveDisplayBounds() getter.

This patch is kept separate from the main Launcher3 desktop patch because it
is a focused rebase-sensitive fix: it touches the configuration-change path,
the InvariantDeviceProfile refresh surface, the taskbar popup anchor and
clamp paths, the taskbar recreate-trigger surface, and the taskbar window-
size helper, while leaving the broader desktop shell behavior in the main
patch.

Applies on top of packages-apps-Launcher3.patch.

diff --git a/quickstep/src/com/android/launcher3/taskbar/TaskbarManagerImpl.java b/quickstep/src/com/android/launcher3/taskbar/TaskbarManagerImpl.java
index 93d40b7e7e..c374fc63fe 100644
--- a/quickstep/src/com/android/launcher3/taskbar/TaskbarManagerImpl.java
+++ b/quickstep/src/com/android/launcher3/taskbar/TaskbarManagerImpl.java
@@ -154,16 +154,23 @@
      * This includes all the configurations defined in Launcher's manifest entry and
      * ActivityController#filterConfigChanges
      */
+    // Fix 2e: let desktop/freeform displays recreate the taskbar on dynamic
+    // size/orientation changes, then mask these bits again below for
+    // non-desktop displays. Upstream suppresses them to keep the taskbar window
+    // alive across rotations on phones; on desktop the taskbar's mAttrs
+    // (notably the fillx<N> height) is baked in at window-create time.
     private static final int SKIP_RECREATE_CONFIG_CHANGES = ActivityInfo.CONFIG_WINDOW_CONFIGURATION
             | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_KEYBOARD
             | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_KEYBOARD_HIDDEN
             | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_MCC
             | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_MNC
-            | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_NAVIGATION
-            | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_ORIENTATION
-            | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_SCREEN_SIZE
-            | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_SCREEN_LAYOUT
-            | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_SMALLEST_SCREEN_SIZE;
+            | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_NAVIGATION;
+
+    private static final int DESKTOP_DYNAMIC_DISPLAY_CONFIG_CHANGES =
+            ActivityInfo.CONFIG_ORIENTATION
+                    | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_SCREEN_SIZE
+                    | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_SCREEN_LAYOUT
+                    | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_SMALLEST_SCREEN_SIZE;

     private static final Uri USER_SETUP_COMPLETE_URI = Settings.Secure.getUriFor(
             Settings.Secure.USER_SETUP_COMPLETE);
@@ -1547,6 +1554,33 @@
                 }
                 DeviceProfile dp = getDeviceProfile(displayId);
                 int configDiff = mOldConfig.diff(newConfig) & ~SKIP_RECREATE_CONFIG_CHANGES;
+                boolean isDesktopDynamicDisplay = displayId == mPrimaryDisplayId
+                        && com.android.launcher3.util.DisplayController
+                                .showDesktopTaskbarForFreeformDisplay(mPrimaryWindowContext);
+                if (!isDesktopDynamicDisplay) {
+                    configDiff &= ~DESKTOP_DYNAMIC_DISPLAY_CONFIG_CHANGES;
+                }
+                boolean displayMetricsChanged =
+                        mOldConfig.screenWidthDp != newConfig.screenWidthDp
+                                || mOldConfig.screenHeightDp != newConfig.screenHeightDp
+                                || mOldConfig.smallestScreenWidthDp
+                                        != newConfig.smallestScreenWidthDp
+                                || mOldConfig.densityDpi != newConfig.densityDpi
+                                || (configDiff
+                                        & (ActivityInfo.CONFIG_DENSITY
+                                                | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_SCREEN_SIZE
+                                                | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_SCREEN_LAYOUT
+                                                | ActivityInfo.CONFIG_SMALLEST_SCREEN_SIZE)) != 0;
+                if (isDesktopDynamicDisplay && (displayMetricsChanged || dp == null)) {
+                    LauncherAppState.getIDP(mPrimaryWindowContext).refreshAfterDisplayChange();
+                    dp = getDeviceProfile(displayId);
+                    // Fix 2a: push the refreshed DP into the all-apps container so its
+                    // per-row count tracks the new geometry, not the cached one.
+                    Launcher launcher = Launcher.ACTIVITY_TRACKER.getCreatedContext();
+                    if (launcher != null && dp != null && launcher.getAppsView() != null) {
+                        launcher.getAppsView().onDeviceProfileChanged(dp);
+                    }
+                }

                 if ((configDiff & ActivityInfo.CONFIG_UI_MODE) != 0) {
                     debugTaskbarManager("onConfigurationChanged: theme changed", displayId);
